job_summary:
ADW Johnson Pty Ltd is a multi-disciplinary consultancy firm providing Town Planning, Civil Engineering, Project Management and Surveying services to a client base including some of the largest developers in the state as well as a range of Government and infrastructure-related authorities. Our projects typically include residential detached housing subdivisions, multi- unit/apartment developments, seniors living and mobile home developments, industrial subdivisions and major infrastructure projects (roads, intersections, pump stations etc) with our involvement often ranging from the acquisition/due diligence phase through to the registration of developed lots.
ADW Johnson employs in excess of 100 staff across its three (3) offices in Sydney (Barangaroo), Central Coast (Tuggerah) and the Hunter (Warners Bay). Our project locations generally extend from Wollongong in the south, to Coffs Harbour in the north and as far inland as Dubbo.
We are currently seeking a Survey Office Manager with a minimum of five (5) years’ post- registration experience or up to eight (8) years’ post-graduation experience in residential development and infrastructure projects within NSW to join our team.
The successful applicant will primarily be based at our Central Coast (Tuggerah) office, but may ultimately be required to participate in projects anywhere within our broad range of project locations including the possibility for some opportunity to work from our Sydney and Hunter offices. The successful applicant is to provide leadership, coordination and strategic direction to the activities of our Survey business in Tuggerah (Central Coast) in collaboration with the company’s overall Survey Manager and with the wider ADW Johnson business. This senior appointment will provide surveying industry knowledge and effective project management skills plus assume overall responsibility for leading the operations and activities of our Survey teams currently servicing Central Coast and Sydney operating from our Tuggerah office.
In addition to above, we are seeking a highly motivated individual with the following skills and experience:

Tertiary Qualification(s) in surveying and preferably hold current registration with the Board of Surveying and Spatial Information of NSW (BOSSI) as a Registered Land Surveyor;


Strong relevant surveying experience in NSW;


Strong verbal and written communication skills;


Ability to provide key technical expertise across a broad range of high-profile projects. Experience in large infrastructure projects including local government, water servicing agencies, Ausgrid and RMS is beneficial;


Ability to lead and work within a team environment, with a strong focus on interpersonal relationships;


Ability to work within and ensure compliance with a strict Integrated Management System incorporating OH & S, Quality and Environmental Management Systems;


Ability to work towards deadlines and budgets by managing your time efficiently;


Maintaining high technical standards and introducing new technology;


Forward thinking and an optimistic, “can-do” attitude;


A keen and effective interest in business development and client relationships;


Active involvement in supervision, encouragement and mentoring of less-experienced survey staff;


Report to the overall Survey Manager and assist with day to day management and systems implementation and refinement;


A thorough understanding of cadastral surveying principles, guidelines and standards along with a comprehensive understanding of relevant NSW legislation relating to land titling processes is beneficial;


A competent knowledge of the use of computer-based software including AutoCAD, 12d, Microsoft Word, Excel and Project or equivalent is beneficial;


Ability to attend meetings and present in a professional manner, technical advice and recommendations of relevant surveying practices to Project Managers, other staff, clients and stakeholders;

At ADW Johnson we have a strong emphasis on company culture and the successful candidate will need to be of a suitable character to fit seamlessly into our team. This emphasis on creating a good working environment is reflected by our high-staff retention rate and a large number of long- term employees i.e. over 10 years employment with ADW Johnson.
We place a strong emphasis on providing opportunities for career progression and have an internal professional development program for each of our staff which is regularly monitored and updated. This program ensures that each individual’s career aspirations are known and wherever possible their work-related opportunities are reflective of this.
At ADW Johnson we offer the opportunity to work within a professional and friendly environment, collaborating across a team of established professionals on a range of interesting projects whilst assisting with the growth and development of our team. We encourage a fun and enjoyable working environment with easy-going staff and a variety of social event opportunities including boat days, golf days, go-kart days, going to sporting events, Christmas parties, company dinners and functions. We also promote the membership of professional organisations, attendance and contribution to seminars and functions and the continuing professional development of our staff.
We offer the professionalism and benefits of working in a much larger corporation with the atmosphere of the friendly, personal service of a smaller firm. At the same time we undertake large projects within the busy Sydney urban environment without the necessary stress and hassle of actually needing to be based in Sydney along with its associated problems of high costs of living, travel woes and parking problems.
An attractive remuneration package, based upon level of experience and qualifications, will be negotiated with the successful applicant including automatic paid overtime on billable work and the option of inclusion in our flexi-time accrual system and mobile phone & vehicle policies.
Please note that ADW Johnson does not accept unsolicited applications or resumes from recruiters or recruiting agencies.
If you believe that you are the right person for this position, please forward your covering letter and resume, outlining work experience, education & personal attributes along with details of at least two (2) referees to: hunter@adwjohnson.com.au.
